  "text": "In contrast, none of the 8 neurinomas (Fig. 3) , 5 carcin oma metastases, or 3 primary spinal gliomas (1 pilocytic astrocytoma, 1 WHO Grade II astrocytoma, 1 WHO Grade III anaplastic oligoastrocytoma) showed any PpIX fluorescence. Similarly, Eicker et al. reported that all 7 neurinomas included in their study were PpIX negative. [CITATION_1] In contrast to our findings, positive PpIX fluorescence was observed in a patient with a WHO Grade III intramedullary astrocytoma treated with palliative cordectomy. [CITATION_2] Note that 2 of the 3 primary spinal gliomas in our study were classified as low-grade gliomas.",
